headline: Cadence ChipStack AI Super Agent Puts EDA Role In Focus
summary: Cadence Design Systems (NasdaqGS:CDNS) has introduced the ChipStack AI Super Agent, described as a first-of-its-kind agentic AI solution for front-end silicon design and verification. The platform uses multiple virtual engineers powered by Cadence’s existing EDA tools, with the company indicating potential productivity gains of up to tenfold in chip design workflows. headline: Intel AI Push Deepens With SambaNova Bet And New GPU Chief
summary: Intel (NasdaqGS:INTC) is committing at least US$100 million to AI chip startup SambaNova Systems. The company has also appointed former Qualcomm executive Eric Demers as its new Chief GPU Architect. Both moves reflect a shift in how Intel is approaching AI chips and GPU development. Intel, known for its x86 processors and data center products, is increasingly tied to demand for AI computing across cloud, enterprise, and edge use cases.
